-- 
SPAIN DAYBOOK: Savings Bank CAM Presents Capitalization Plan

-- B y   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 
2011-04-11T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/spain-daybook-savings-bank-cam-presents-capitalization-plan.html
Caja de Ahorros del Mediterraneo (CAM) ,
the Spanish savings bank whose planned merger with three other
lenders collapsed, said it presented its recapitalization plan
to the Bank of Spain last week.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*CAM, as the savings bank is known, reiterated it will seek 2.8
billion euros ($4.03 billion) from the government’s bank bailout
fund. The Bank of Spain has set itself a deadline of April 14 to
approve or demand changes to the recapitalization plans of
lenders that need to boost capital ratios.  * Prime Minister Jose Luis Rodriguez Zapatero and Colombian
President Juan Manuel Santos give a news conference at 17:00
CET.  EQUITIES:  * Banco Santander SA (SAN)  Chief Executive Officer Alfredo Saenz  earned 9.18 million euros in fixed and variable pay and  other emoluments in 2010, down from 10.24 million euros the  year earlier, the lender said on its website. Emilio Botin,  the chairman, earned 3.86 million euros, down from 3.99  million euros in 2009, the bank said.  * SOS Corporacion Alimentaria SA is considering cutting  about 150 jobs in  Spain  as part of agreements with its  banks, El Economista reported, without saying where it got  the information.  * London’s Heathrow Airport, which is owned by a  Ferrovial
SA (FER)  led group, imposed a contract exempting itself of blame  in cases of liabilities like last December’s snow, the  Times reported April 9.  *  Repsol YPF SA (REP) ’s Petronor unit said on its Web site it  will shut a unit of its refinery in Bilbao, Spain, for  maintenance that may lead to increased flaring, or the  release of gases into the air.  MARKETS:
*The  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  rose 0.6 percent to 10,913.2.
*The spread between Spanish and German 10-year borrowing costs
narrowed to 178.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Esteban Duarte in Madrid at 
